endable first step.  But don't expect people to take the apology at face value.. expect a long period of time where people will question your motives and actions.  <br><br>It will take a long time to forgive.. and an even longer time to forget, I suspect. (Not to mention you've given those who benefit by bashing you some amount of justification and ability to continue indefinitely without community lashback against them.)<br><br>By indirectly threatening the stability of the community with such a high profile mistake, the lashback was and will continue to be tremendous for you.<br><br>If nothing else, this will be a painful lesson.  Hopefully, it will teach whomever makes decisions such as this to respect the Rathe community as an entity alot more.<br><br><br> <p>Nicolai IronCross<br>Retired Grand Master<br>Knights of the Iron Cross<br>The Rathe<br>nicolai@ironcross.org<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubahimiron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bahimiron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tad-pole</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/25/02 5:15:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=470.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Getting something off my chest</span><hr size=1> Read Dwallyn's log again, Umbali.<br><br>Then tell us that Shei's a good man who just makes mistakes some times.<br><br>'sad, sad'<br><br>Lemme geek out a little bit for a sec, folks:<br><br>&quot;The words of this wizard stand on their heads. In the language of Orthanc help means ruin, and saving means slaying, that is plain.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelag